ODE VIII

TO LYDIA

Y all the gods I charge thee, Lydia, say Wherelore so last through loving slay Thy Sybaris? Patient once of dust and sun The open field now see him shun. A trooper, with his peers he doth not ride, His Gallie steed he doth not guide With dogtooth bit.
